    "These meta-learning mechanisms enable models to swiftly adapt to new knowledge and tasks.",
    "A detailed comparison of representative reliable response generation methods is provided in Table 2.",
    "External Knowledge AugmentationAlthough large language models have demonstrated significant effectiveness in response generation, issues such as susceptibility to hallucinations, difficulty handling in-domain knowledge, and challenges with knowledge updating persist.",
    "Augmenting the model's generative process with external knowledge sources can serve as an effective way to tackle these issues.",
    "Based on the form of external knowledge employed, these approaches can be classified into retrieval augmentation and tool augmentation."
